I have written an example of using a steady-flow reactor in C++, and  
posted it on the wiki. I have also posted a Python script that does  
the same calculuation for comparison.

To get to them, go to the wiki at http://www.cantera.org/wiki,   
select from the navigation list on the left "Community portal", and  
then "Contributed scripts and programs".  Feel free to add scripts/ 
programs of your own to this list if you think they might be useful  
to the user community.

Dave
